Paul Sherman :24 :00 What factors are taken into account when my property is reassessed? If you own a commercial property, most jurisdictions, including Washington, , will utilize some combination of the three (3) primary approaches to real estate 1) An income approach, which values your property based on the income generated from leasing, less the expense required to operate the 2) There is also the cost approach, which determines the value of the land plus the replacement cost (less depreciation) of the structures on the 3) The final approach is the sales comparison This approach analyzes sales of comparable properties to determine the value of your For traditional residential properties like single family homes, condos, and townhomes, the sales comparison approach is fairly standard, while the income approach is most common for commercial and income producing How does Taxonics get my property’s assessment each year when I register for PROTECT? future career opportunities and internships in blockchain Immutable Scholar NFT upon completion, with lifetime membership to Atlanta Blockchain Center ecosystem Network and interact with industry veterans at the Atlanta Blockchain Center, Atlanta’s first blockchain incubator and coworking space Academic Enrichment Students will complete Immutable Scholars with a deeper understanding of blockchain technology and its impact on the They will establish relevant technical skills, develop personal connections and build a network of Programming will cover emerging blockchain disciplines Appointments of industry veterans enhance depth and breadth of expertise across True Environmental’s platform NEW YORK–( BUSINESS WIRE )–True Environmental (“True” or the “Company”), a platform focused on partnering with founder and environmental consulting and engineering firms to provide capital solutions, today announced that Neal Weitman and Dean Harwood have joined the Company as Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer, Weitman is an accomplished professional who possesses more than years of experience, spanning projects across the transportation, infrastructure, water, and environmental end markets for government agencies and private Over the last decade, Weitman has held executive leadership roles with WSP, a leading professional services firm, and predecessor Neal brings successful M&A experience and recognizes the key to all successful mergers is an appreciation for the acquired entities’ cultures, investment in and retention of staff, and supporting initiatives focused on growth to achieve Weitman also worked closely with Jim Stamatis, CEO of True, for more than years while at Louis Berger, prior to the company’s sale to Earlier in his career, Weitman was President and CEO of Berger, Lehman Associates, an engineering and consulting company specializing in critical, large infrastructure Harwood brings more than two decades of experience across the environmental consulting and engineering industry to He joins the Company from Environmental Consulting and Technology, (“ECT”), where he served as Chief Financial Officer and a member of the company’s Board of Prior to ECT, he served as President of Strategy and Development for the western region at Wood plc (LSE: WG), a leader in the delivery of project management, engineering, construction, consulting, and industrial services to customers across a variety of end Before that, Harwood spent years in various senior roles at Parsons Corporation (NYSE: PSN), including Business Unit Chief Financial Officer and eventually Executive Vice President of Operations and President of Parsons Jim Stamatis, CEO of True Environmental, said, “Neal and Dean are both extremely talented and seasoned senior executives in the environmental consulting and engineering I am confident they will bring a wealth of experience and expertise to True as we continue to build our platform and seek to deliver solutions to help solve clients’ complex environmental, infrastructure, and energy I could not be more excited to partner with Neal and Dean as we work to achieve our ” The appointments of Weitman and Harwood follow True’s recently announced partnership with Matrix New World, a leading provider of environmental consulting, engineering, and infrastructure About True Environmental True services and business consumer The firm partners with experienced management teams to build businesses in highly fragmented markets with durable secular For more information, please visit .
